housewife, mother and part-time prostitute over the course of three days; on the side of form, it rigorously records her domestic routine in extended time and from a fixed camera position. In a film that, agonisingly, depicts women’s oppression, Akerman transforms cinema, itself so often an instrument of women’s oppression, into a liberating force.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read the <a href=\"https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/features/greatest-film-all-time-jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles\">full article by Laura Mulvey</a></p>\r\n","quote":null,"credits":{"director":"Chantal Akerman","producer":"Evelyne Paul, Corinne Jenart","writer":"Chantal Akerman","featuring":"Delphine Seyrig, Jan Decorte, Henri Storck"},"year":"1975","nameAndYear":"Jeanne Dielman, 23 Quai du Commerce, 1080 Bruxelles (1975)","links":{"player":"https://player.bfi.org.uk/subscription/film/watch-jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles-1975-online","southbank":""},"player":{"url":"https://player.bfi.org.uk/subscription/film/watch-jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles-1975-online","cta":"https://player.bfi.org.uk/subscribe/15785","pillar":"subscription","price":0,"duration":0},"performances":[],"tags":["BFI Player"],"productionCountries":"Belgium, France","runningTime":201,"sightAndSound":{"results":[{"position":1,"tied":false,"category":"critics"},{"position":4,"tied":true,"category":"directors"}],"voters":{"critics":[{"firstname":"Neta","surname":"Alexander","slug":"neta-alexander","name":"Neta Alexander","sortName":"Alexander, Neta","type":"critic","jobTitle":"Assistant Professor of Film and Media, Colgate University ","country":"USA","remarks":null,"url":"/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/neta-alexander"},{"firstname":"Jonathan","surname":"Ali","slug":"jonathan-ali","name":"Jonathan Ali","sortName":"Ali, Jonathan","type":"critic","jobTitle":"Film programmer","country":"UK","remarks":null,"url":"/sight-and-sound/greatest-films-all-time/all-voters/